Introduction

This the an API doc for the JustBnb project (SPA)

Base URL: http://laravel-vue-spa.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Endpoints

POST api/login

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"azboncak@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"H`cP8u0v4!AI;z!1RS\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "azboncak@example.net",
    "password": "H`cP8u0v4!AI;z!1RS"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/login

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Example: azboncak@example.net

password   string   

Example: HcP8u0v4!AI;z!1RS`

POST api/register

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"mdrmgxouqaeqvnksikmeaxk\",
    \"email\": \"brooke.stokes@example.net\",
    \"password\": \"PFve>N&CUh`(\\/\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "mdrmgxouqaeqvnksikmeaxk",
    "email": "brooke.stokes@example.net",
    "password": "PFve>N&CUh`(\/"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: mdrmgxouqaeqvnksikmeaxk

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: brooke.stokes@example.net

password   string   

Must be at least 6 characters. Example: PFve>N&CUh(/`

POST api/logout

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/logout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Display a listing of the resource.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/bookables" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/bookables"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
